WEBVTT

00:06.080 --> 00:08.080
[birds chirping]

00:29.760 --> 00:32.320
Molisho!

00:32.360 --> 00:33.720
What are you doing?

00:33.760 --> 00:35.720
Running.

00:35.760 --> 00:37.000
If they find you...

00:37.040 --> 00:40.040
Are you going to stop me?

00:56.800 --> 00:59.480
♪ ♪

01:20.880 --> 01:22.880
[phone ringing]

01:28.280 --> 01:30.240
[sniffles]

01:30.280 --> 01:33.520
Oh, God.

01:33.560 --> 01:35.000
Hello?

01:37.520 --> 01:40.280
Who is this?

01:44.360 --> 01:46.160
[crying]

01:46.200 --> 01:48.160
Georgia?

01:48.200 --> 01:50.480
Wha...

01:50.520 --> 01:52.120
What's happened?

01:52.160 --> 01:55.240
Someone killed Emmanuel.

01:55.280 --> 01:58.280
They sent a rental car
for me, and...

01:58.320 --> 02:00.800
and there was a bomb in it.

02:00.840 --> 02:02.240
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

02:02.280 --> 02:05.440
No. No, I'm fine.

02:05.480 --> 02:08.800
Right. I want you to get on
the first plane out of there

02:08.840 --> 02:12.200
-and get back here now.
-No.

02:12.240 --> 02:15.200
It isn't just
about Will anymore.

02:15.240 --> 02:18.040
It's about Emmanuel.

02:18.080 --> 02:21.280
I'm going to Kisima tomorrow
with Judith.

02:21.320 --> 02:23.200
That's not a good idea.

02:23.240 --> 02:25.720
Look, I know what you think
of me being out here,

02:25.760 --> 02:28.400
but things have changed.
My friend is dead.

02:28.440 --> 02:31.280
I need to find Pieter Bello
and I need you to help me.

02:31.320 --> 02:34.400
Please, Martin.

02:34.440 --> 02:37.880
[crying]

02:41.600 --> 02:43.240
DOCTOR:
Mr. Helgason.

02:43.280 --> 02:46.400
Thank you for coming in
on such short notice.

02:46.440 --> 02:48.840
ARIEL:
Of course.

02:48.880 --> 02:52.200
Uh, when we met,
we discussed the criteria

02:52.240 --> 02:55.200
we needed for the trial.

02:55.240 --> 02:58.040
We are, uh, looking
for specific qualities,

02:58.080 --> 03:00.560
specific conditions, in patients

03:00.600 --> 03:04.960
that will indicate results
best to help our research.

03:05.000 --> 03:07.760
And, um, I'm sorry,
but in your instance,

03:07.800 --> 03:10.920
we will not be able
to perform the surgery.

03:14.520 --> 03:16.680
[clears throat]

03:16.720 --> 03:18.440
I don't understand.

03:18.480 --> 03:22.120
Well, the-the damage
to the optic nerve,

03:22.160 --> 03:27.440
um, there are parameters. Yeah?

03:27.480 --> 03:30.240
And other patients who fit these
parameters more closely...

03:30.280 --> 03:33.000
Well, okay,
so you've changed the rules.

03:33.040 --> 03:35.040
You are afraid
I will affect your results.

03:35.080 --> 03:39.440
Well, I wish, Mr. Helgason,
that I had better news.

03:39.480 --> 03:41.720
[stammers] There are
a number of other trials,

03:41.760 --> 03:43.920
other surgeons working
in this field.

03:43.960 --> 03:46.840
Yeah, but none of them are you.

03:46.880 --> 03:51.560
I am not a religious man.
Not anymore.

03:51.600 --> 03:54.160
But then, I hear of you.

03:54.200 --> 03:58.240
A man who works miracles, a man
who gives sight to the blind.

03:58.280 --> 04:02.240
And I fly here
with money I don't have,

04:02.280 --> 04:05.240
and I am reminded once again

04:05.280 --> 04:09.960
of why I decided that faith was
a waste of my damn time.

04:11.640 --> 04:13.040
[quietly]:
Listen, I...

04:13.080 --> 04:15.080
♪ ♪

04:28.080 --> 04:30.120
[crying]

04:58.080 --> 05:00.240
[insects chirping]

05:14.400 --> 05:16.360
[plane flying in distance]

05:16.400 --> 05:19.080
[camera shutter clicking]

05:30.520 --> 05:32.520
[speaking French]

05:32.560 --> 05:34.000
-Okay?
-GAELLE: Hey!

05:45.680 --> 05:47.000
[Will speaking softly]

05:47.040 --> 05:48.800
-[pencil drops]
-Oh, shit.

05:50.680 --> 05:52.080
Thank you.

05:54.880 --> 05:57.000
Hey, uh...

05:57.040 --> 06:00.520
Hi, I'm checking in, Kinshasa...

06:01.560 --> 06:03.920
[electronic chime]

06:07.320 --> 06:08.960
[electronic chime]

06:10.520 --> 06:12.480
[children laughing]

06:12.520 --> 06:14.760
-[grunts]
-Pardon.

06:14.800 --> 06:17.760
It's-it's okay. It's okay.
Um, excusez-moi.

06:17.800 --> 06:20.600
Pardonnez-moi.

06:22.680 --> 06:24.960
Ow.

06:27.400 --> 06:29.400
[indistinct chatter]

06:37.520 --> 06:40.320
[grunts]
Ow.

06:40.360 --> 06:42.240
Ouch.

06:42.280 --> 06:45.480
I know. It's burned to a crisp.

06:47.640 --> 06:49.920
I was, uh, I was wearing
a long-sleeved T-shirt,

06:49.960 --> 06:53.120
but, um, well,
it was really hot outside,

06:53.160 --> 06:54.720
so I rolled up the sleeves.

06:54.760 --> 06:57.440
[both laugh]

06:57.480 --> 06:59.560
Uh, hi, I'm Mikael.
I'm an idiot.

06:59.600 --> 07:01.320
Dominique.

07:01.360 --> 07:04.360
Nice to meet you.

07:13.040 --> 07:15.040
[beeping]

07:19.040 --> 07:20.640
[beeping continues]

07:26.720 --> 07:28.240
Oh, uh...

07:28.280 --> 07:30.000
Oh...

07:30.040 --> 07:32.000
Um...

07:32.040 --> 07:35.320
Madam-Mademoiselle, um,
your bag, uh, le sac.

07:35.360 --> 07:36.720
Uh, beep, beep.

07:36.760 --> 07:39.080
Alarm.
[chuckles]

07:39.120 --> 07:41.240
[beeping]

07:46.160 --> 07:47.320
[clears throat]

07:47.360 --> 07:48.520
[electronic chime]

07:48.560 --> 07:49.920
[speaks French]
Your seat.

07:49.960 --> 07:51.120
Oh, um...

07:51.160 --> 07:53.400
[woman speaking French
over P.A.]

07:57.120 --> 07:59.480
[beeping]

08:09.400 --> 08:11.040
[grunts]

08:13.040 --> 08:14.080
[seatbelt clicks]

08:14.120 --> 08:16.960
[beeping]

08:18.040 --> 08:19.440
[people screaming]

08:20.480 --> 08:22.400
[moaning]

08:36.360 --> 08:39.040
[hyperventilating]

08:53.800 --> 08:58.040
How many times have I told you?

08:58.080 --> 09:00.360
The window is open.

09:00.400 --> 09:02.600
I can smell that bloody thing
from upstairs.

09:02.640 --> 09:04.400
Put it out.

09:04.440 --> 09:05.960
You know it's not good
for your hay fever.

09:06.000 --> 09:07.640
[coughs, sneezes]

09:07.680 --> 09:10.080
What's going on with you?

09:10.120 --> 09:13.480
Georgia called again.

09:13.520 --> 09:15.720
What happened?

09:15.760 --> 09:17.600
Things have got complicated.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.680
She needs your help?

09:19.720 --> 09:21.360
Yeah.

09:21.400 --> 09:23.400
Well, for Christ's sakes,
help her.

09:23.440 --> 09:25.840
If anyone has
the resources, it's you.

09:25.880 --> 09:27.840
She is convinced that Will

09:27.880 --> 09:30.600
is somehow still alive,
and she's wrong.

09:30.640 --> 09:33.680
Except you're starting
to wonder if she isn't.

09:33.720 --> 09:38.440
Someone died in a car bomb
that was meant for her.

09:38.480 --> 09:41.320
But she won't come back.

09:41.360 --> 09:43.520
My God, she's stubborn.

09:43.560 --> 09:45.920
She's been on her own
for too long.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.040
You're not the reason
for that, love.

09:48.080 --> 09:50.440
You have to stop
blaming yourself.

09:50.480 --> 09:54.080
Well, I didn't help her
when she needed me.

09:54.120 --> 09:55.720
Well, you can sit here
feeling sorry for yourself,

09:55.760 --> 09:57.960
or you can get up off
of your arse and help.

09:58.000 --> 10:01.640
Either way,
put that bloody thing out.

10:06.720 --> 10:08.720
[exhales]

10:18.360 --> 10:20.360
It's around here.

10:20.400 --> 10:22.360
Sorry?

10:22.400 --> 10:24.040
Uh, this is the route he took,

10:24.080 --> 10:26.560
coming the other way,
Goma to Kinshasa,

10:26.600 --> 10:28.520
but he would have
gone over this.

10:28.560 --> 10:31.600
Somewhere there, that's where
Will's plane went down.

10:31.640 --> 10:35.120
It's hard to imagine.

10:37.560 --> 10:40.520
It's so beautiful,

10:40.560 --> 10:43.520
but there's such darkness
beneath it.

10:47.960 --> 10:49.960
[insects chirping]

11:17.040 --> 11:20.440
[Ariel groaning]

11:30.920 --> 11:32.560
[gasps]

11:32.600 --> 11:35.680
Ah. Ah.

11:35.720 --> 11:37.880
[groaning]

11:49.280 --> 11:51.320
I thought you were dead.

11:51.360 --> 11:53.880
I thought...
Oh, I can't believe it.

11:53.920 --> 11:56.360
-Oh. [groans]
-I can't believe it.

11:56.400 --> 11:57.960
-The two of us.
-Yeah.

11:58.000 --> 12:00.840
-I can't believe it.
-Yeah. [groans]

12:05.880 --> 12:07.280
The plane.

12:10.200 --> 12:11.840
No, no. No, no.

12:11.880 --> 12:14.160
There is...

12:14.200 --> 12:18.880
there is no one alive here.

12:18.920 --> 12:21.920
-There is no one. [crying]
-[groaning]

12:25.920 --> 12:28.040
C-Can you walk?

12:28.080 --> 12:31.040
[groans] Sure, just about.

12:31.080 --> 12:33.080
We need to get out of here.

12:36.080 --> 12:41.000
But... maybe we should,
maybe we should wait till light.

12:41.040 --> 12:43.800
No. We must find the rest
of the plane.

12:43.840 --> 12:45.800
-Yeah.
-See if, uh,

12:45.840 --> 12:49.720
if anyone else survived.
Come. Can-can you?

12:49.760 --> 12:53.200
-Yeah. I'm fine.
-Okay.

12:53.240 --> 12:55.360
-ARIEL: So fine.
-Okay.

12:55.400 --> 12:57.400
♪ ♪

13:03.200 --> 13:07.360
Good news, it looks like someone
will take you today.

13:07.400 --> 13:08.840
Great. Who?

13:08.880 --> 13:10.960
You know, uh,
all the NGOs in this area,

13:11.000 --> 13:12.440
they-they all
look after each other,

13:12.480 --> 13:15.880
so I put word out and it seems
like there's a medical truck

13:15.920 --> 13:20.640
heading through Kisima,
measles vaccination program.

13:20.680 --> 13:22.480
I told them you were
a journalist,

13:22.520 --> 13:24.160
writing about their work
in the region.

13:24.200 --> 13:25.400
Thank you.

13:44.520 --> 13:47.560
Eh! Bonjour.

13:47.600 --> 13:50.640
[both speaking French]

13:53.520 --> 13:55.840
-Hello!
-Hello.

14:15.440 --> 14:16.880
JUDITH:
He did them on that trip.

14:16.920 --> 14:18.280
On that last trip?

14:18.320 --> 14:20.720
Yeah.

14:20.760 --> 14:23.920
Oh, God, it was the biggest
bastard of a storm.

14:23.960 --> 14:25.760
Will got stuck in the office.

14:25.800 --> 14:28.680
There was no phone, no Internet.

14:28.720 --> 14:31.000
So he drew those.

14:31.040 --> 14:34.320
I couldn't take them down.

14:34.360 --> 14:36.480
GEORGIA: Would you mind
if I kept this one?

14:36.520 --> 14:40.000
Oh, my God, of course.

14:45.880 --> 14:47.960
[clears throat]

14:48.000 --> 14:50.280
Look, the militia groups
out where you're going,

14:50.320 --> 14:53.960
they should leave you be,
and as far as they're concerned,

14:54.000 --> 14:57.200
you're out there
vaccinating against disease,

14:57.240 --> 14:59.800
-but I can't guarantee anything.
-I know.

14:59.840 --> 15:02.120
I really appreciate
you getting me here.

15:07.840 --> 15:10.600
I don't know what you're
gonna find out there,

15:10.640 --> 15:12.080
but Will meant a lot to me,

15:12.120 --> 15:15.240
and that's the only reason why
I haven't told you this--

15:15.280 --> 15:18.320
Christ knows maybe
it's best not to, but...

15:18.360 --> 15:19.640
What?

15:19.680 --> 15:21.520
Jud-- what are you
talking about?

15:23.080 --> 15:24.880
I don't want you
to think that I've held

15:24.920 --> 15:28.000
anything back from you, okay?

15:28.040 --> 15:29.400
I heard there was a woman.

15:29.440 --> 15:33.960
Apparently it happened
a few months before the crash.

15:34.000 --> 15:38.120
I don't think it was anything
serious, not for Will,

15:38.160 --> 15:41.320
except that the woman
was the wife of a general

15:41.360 --> 15:43.800
in the Congolese army,
and apparently,

15:43.840 --> 15:47.680
Will was terrified
that he might find out.

15:56.640 --> 15:58.360
I'm sorry.

15:59.400 --> 16:02.840
And... and he t-- he told you.

16:04.000 --> 16:06.000
Um...

16:06.040 --> 16:09.240
Did Will tell you
he was having an affair?

16:09.280 --> 16:11.760
No.

16:11.800 --> 16:14.040
But when you work with someone,
you hear things...

16:14.080 --> 16:15.520
Right, so it was a rumor.

16:15.560 --> 16:16.880
You don't know.

16:16.920 --> 16:19.000
They were seen having supper
together, so...

16:19.040 --> 16:20.680
Yeah, but that's
office gossip, Judith.

16:20.720 --> 16:23.000
That's people stirring the pot

16:23.040 --> 16:25.320
because they're bored.

16:25.360 --> 16:28.160
He wouldn't.
He wouldn't do that.

16:28.200 --> 16:30.520
Just listen for a minute, okay?

16:30.560 --> 16:33.640
If someone has taken Will
prisoner... [chuckles]

16:33.680 --> 16:35.040
then why?

16:35.080 --> 16:38.440
What if he did dishonor
this general?

16:38.480 --> 16:40.840
What has that got to do
with a crashed plane?!

16:40.880 --> 16:43.320
And how the hell my husband
walked off it alive?

16:43.360 --> 16:46.280
I know. And I want answers,
just like you do.

16:46.320 --> 16:48.240
But I also want you
to know the truth.

16:48.280 --> 16:52.040
But I want to tell you
everything.

16:52.080 --> 16:55.680
You know, you want answers.

16:55.720 --> 16:57.680
You have to ask questions.

16:59.640 --> 17:01.640
[sighs]

17:04.360 --> 17:06.400
I think you should go back
to work.

17:21.680 --> 17:23.680
♪ ♪

17:31.840 --> 17:33.680
[speaking Swahili]

17:33.720 --> 17:35.480
-Where are we going?
-No idea.

17:35.520 --> 17:38.440
You should ask fewer questions,
Adidja.

17:38.480 --> 17:40.480
It's easier that way.

17:54.240 --> 17:56.240
[sound of rooster crowing]

17:58.120 --> 18:00.320
[phone beeps]

18:00.360 --> 18:02.720
Francais?

18:02.760 --> 18:05.240
[pills rattle]

18:11.000 --> 18:13.160
My Swahili's for shit.

18:13.200 --> 18:17.040
That's what happens
when you rely on translators.

18:17.080 --> 18:18.560
English?

18:18.600 --> 18:20.640
-Some.
-So how did you learn?

18:20.680 --> 18:22.680
Radio? TV?

18:22.720 --> 18:24.200
The UN.

18:24.240 --> 18:26.960
There was a station near
my village...

18:27.000 --> 18:28.760
a long time ago.

18:28.800 --> 18:31.840
I have a daughter
about your age.

18:31.880 --> 18:33.840
It was her birthday
the other day.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.400
I sent her a present.

18:35.440 --> 18:37.440
A little plastic kitchen.

18:37.480 --> 18:40.240
Her mother...

18:40.280 --> 18:41.880
Bitch sent it back.

18:41.920 --> 18:45.240
She said I don't understand
what she likes.

18:45.280 --> 18:47.640
Too young for her.

18:47.680 --> 18:49.600
So she wrapped up something...

18:49.640 --> 18:52.160
told my daughter it was from me.

18:54.160 --> 18:56.600
This, all of this is for her.

18:56.640 --> 19:01.800
Protecting someone's innocence
is... is an ugly business.

19:08.920 --> 19:12.080
I saw you let your friend go.

19:12.120 --> 19:13.600
It's okay.

19:13.640 --> 19:15.960
I won't tell anyone.

19:16.000 --> 19:20.320
Thank you. [sighs]

19:20.360 --> 19:22.880
What's your name?

19:22.920 --> 19:26.600
-Adidja.
-Adidja.

19:26.640 --> 19:29.440
Adidja, listen to me.

19:29.480 --> 19:32.440
When we get where we're going,
you're going to do something

19:32.480 --> 19:34.680
for me the same way
I did something for you.

19:34.720 --> 19:36.320
Okay?

19:45.920 --> 19:47.920
[vehicle approaching]

19:52.400 --> 19:54.320
[car door opens, closes]

19:54.360 --> 19:56.680
You must be Georgia.

19:56.720 --> 19:58.120
Yeah.

19:58.160 --> 19:59.680
Tom Jenson.

19:59.720 --> 20:01.920
Hashtag doctor, hashtag legend.

20:01.960 --> 20:04.640
[laughs] You're one of those.

20:04.680 --> 20:06.280
[laughs] Who do you write for?

20:06.320 --> 20:08.760
Whoever writes me a check.

20:08.800 --> 20:09.960
JUDITH:
Right.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.560
You're off then.

20:11.600 --> 20:14.600
-Uh, Judith.
-Tom.

20:14.640 --> 20:16.600
I hope you don't mind me
calling in this favor

20:16.640 --> 20:18.200
-with your supervisor.
-It's fine. Really.

20:18.240 --> 20:21.000
-You'll look after her, yeah?
-Of course. As long as you know

20:21.040 --> 20:22.680
where you're going out there,
it's not a problem.

20:22.720 --> 20:25.080
-Yeah, right.
-[laughs]

20:26.800 --> 20:30.880
[speaking French]

20:32.720 --> 20:34.320
We ready?

20:34.360 --> 20:36.520
I am.

20:38.520 --> 20:40.200
Don't do anything silly, okay?

20:40.240 --> 20:41.880
-I need answers.
-Me, too.

20:45.520 --> 20:47.200
-Hi. I'm Georgia.
-Fabrice.

20:47.240 --> 20:48.720
Welcome, Georgia.

20:48.760 --> 20:49.720
Let's get going.

20:49.760 --> 20:52.400
This is Louise,
our project coordinator.

20:52.440 --> 20:53.800
Don't take offense at her.

20:53.840 --> 20:55.480
She's been doing this forever.

20:55.520 --> 20:57.200
Too many years out here,
she's forgotten how to be nice.

20:57.240 --> 20:59.080
Right, are we going or what?

20:59.120 --> 21:01.040
[continues in French]

21:03.880 --> 21:05.600
You speak French?

21:05.640 --> 21:07.280
-Not really.
-Oh.

21:07.320 --> 21:09.440
Probably for the best.

21:09.480 --> 21:11.800
-Is the first stop Kisima?
-Mm-hmm.

21:11.840 --> 21:14.080
Yeah. About four
or five hours from here.

21:14.120 --> 21:15.280
Or, usually.

21:15.320 --> 21:16.480
[French hip-hop playing
on radio]

21:16.520 --> 21:18.280
But if you don't like
French hip-hop,

21:18.320 --> 21:19.600
it'll feel like ten.

21:19.640 --> 21:22.080
-[laughs]
-[engine starts]

21:23.360 --> 21:24.920
Don't touch me!

21:24.960 --> 21:26.960
[Tom and Fabrice laugh]

21:36.040 --> 21:38.040
[sighs]

21:46.080 --> 21:48.080
♪ ♪

21:55.840 --> 21:57.840
[Ariel groans]

22:01.480 --> 22:03.440
[grunts]

22:03.480 --> 22:04.960
DOMINIQUE:
How's the pain?

22:05.000 --> 22:06.480
Ah...
[sniffs]

22:06.520 --> 22:08.480
you mean the sunburn?
[chuckles]

22:08.520 --> 22:10.240
It's getting better.

22:10.280 --> 22:11.960
Oh. I...

22:12.000 --> 22:14.800
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

22:14.840 --> 22:16.600
[panting, wincing]

22:16.640 --> 22:19.280
[groaning]

22:19.320 --> 22:21.880
Can you try to go further?

22:21.920 --> 22:23.920
[groaning]

22:25.320 --> 22:28.040
God knows how long
we've been walking.

22:28.080 --> 22:30.040
We've seen no one, nothing.

22:30.080 --> 22:32.280
[Ariel coughing]

22:36.000 --> 22:39.000
[coughing, hacking]

22:41.120 --> 22:42.520
I'm sorry.

22:42.560 --> 22:45.760
I just feel... feel so weak.

22:45.800 --> 22:48.640
Yeah. We need
to get you some water.

22:48.680 --> 22:51.880
Uh, how-how...
how do you feel?

22:51.920 --> 22:53.120
[sighs]

22:53.160 --> 22:55.760
Tired, scared.

22:55.800 --> 22:57.560
But lucky.

22:57.600 --> 23:00.200
It is a miracle
that we are even here.

23:00.240 --> 23:03.200
God is...
God is looking down on us.

23:03.240 --> 23:05.120
[chuckles]:
Well...

23:05.160 --> 23:07.120
he didn't look out enough.

23:07.160 --> 23:08.680
[Ariel grunting]

23:08.720 --> 23:10.920
Did you see what happened?

23:10.960 --> 23:14.360
No. I just heard the explosion.

23:14.400 --> 23:16.600
It was a woman.

23:16.640 --> 23:19.240
Near the front. Pregnant.

23:19.280 --> 23:21.240
She had a laptop, and...

23:21.280 --> 23:23.240
when she... when she opened it,

23:23.280 --> 23:25.440
it just...

23:25.480 --> 23:27.040
boom.

23:27.080 --> 23:28.840
-Wha...?
-I...

23:28.880 --> 23:30.800
I saw her before.

23:30.840 --> 23:33.280
She was...
she was given the bag.

23:33.320 --> 23:35.720
I-I don't believe she knew
what was inside.

23:35.760 --> 23:38.080
This is crazy.

23:38.120 --> 23:40.040
Come on.

23:40.080 --> 23:41.440
-Make a move.
-No, no, you.

23:41.480 --> 23:43.240
Even if we find some shelter.

23:43.280 --> 23:45.440
Y-You go, you go.

23:45.480 --> 23:48.680
You go. You can walk
much further than I c...

23:48.720 --> 23:49.920
I can.

23:49.960 --> 23:52.040
-I'll only slow you down.
-No.

23:52.080 --> 23:54.600
No. I am not going without you.

23:54.640 --> 23:56.720
-Come!
-Please, please, please.

23:58.080 --> 24:00.400
[crying]:
Please.

24:00.440 --> 24:02.160
I want you to go.

24:02.200 --> 24:04.520
-[sniffles] Please go.
-Okay.

24:04.560 --> 24:06.400
[whispers]:
I will get someone.

24:06.440 --> 24:08.440
I will, I will get help.

24:10.000 --> 24:12.040
[trembling exhale]

24:12.080 --> 24:13.920
I'll find someone.

24:13.960 --> 24:17.120
When you get out of here,
you'll-you'll tell them.

24:17.160 --> 24:19.200
Tell them about the woman.

24:19.240 --> 24:20.960
And the laptop.

24:21.000 --> 24:23.560
People... people need to know
what happened here.

24:23.600 --> 24:25.680
I will.

24:25.720 --> 24:27.080
[Ariel sniffles]

24:27.120 --> 24:28.960
[insects chirping]

24:29.000 --> 24:31.320
Dominique.

24:31.360 --> 24:33.600
Please...

24:33.640 --> 24:36.080
please remember the aftersun.

24:36.120 --> 24:39.120
[pained, gasping grunts]

24:44.680 --> 24:47.080
[quiet, gasping breaths]

24:53.080 --> 24:55.280
♪ ♪

25:13.480 --> 25:16.840
-[gasps loudly]
-[gasps, speaks Swahili]

25:16.880 --> 25:19.600
[weakly]:
Help.

25:21.160 --> 25:22.320
[gasping breath]

25:22.360 --> 25:25.080
No. No.

25:25.120 --> 25:26.520
[groans]

25:26.560 --> 25:28.800
[mumbles]

25:30.320 --> 25:32.360
[speaks Swahili]

25:49.480 --> 25:51.480
♪ ♪

25:53.480 --> 25:55.680
[grunting weakly]

26:01.720 --> 26:03.960
[continues grunting weakly]

26:14.680 --> 26:16.880
[groans]

26:18.880 --> 26:20.520
[Ariel coughs]

26:29.280 --> 26:32.080
[low groaning]

26:32.120 --> 26:35.000
-[door opens]
-[indistinct chatter]

26:35.040 --> 26:40.160
[pained groaning]

26:40.200 --> 26:42.920
Ah, you're finally awake, sir.

26:46.800 --> 26:48.200
I'm sorry, my...

26:48.240 --> 26:50.640
[woman speaks French]

26:55.000 --> 26:57.440
[gags]

26:57.480 --> 26:58.840
[gasps]

26:58.880 --> 27:00.880
[pants]

27:02.440 --> 27:06.240
I'm sorry, my French
is not so good.

27:06.280 --> 27:08.320
-You are English?
-No.

27:08.360 --> 27:09.920
Icelandic.

27:09.960 --> 27:12.200
Ah. It's good to see you awake.

27:12.240 --> 27:14.200
I am Dr. Pascal Bourg.

27:14.240 --> 27:15.400
Mikael.

27:15.440 --> 27:17.040
Nice to meet you, Mikael.

27:17.080 --> 27:19.360
You are in Heal Africa
Hospital in Goma.

27:19.400 --> 27:21.760
You were not a well man
when you came in.

27:21.800 --> 27:23.200
Internal bleeding.

27:23.240 --> 27:25.480
We had to drain the blood
with a chest tube.

27:25.520 --> 27:28.280
We made a transfusion.
I found five broken ribs,

27:28.320 --> 27:30.800
your lungs had collapsed,
and a...

27:30.840 --> 27:32.120
severely lacerated kidney.

27:32.160 --> 27:34.000
This, I am afraid,
we had to remove.

27:34.040 --> 27:36.880
-[whimpers]
-And yet here you are, hmm?

27:38.400 --> 27:41.080
Tha... Thank you.
[grunts]

27:41.120 --> 27:43.480
We have a surgeon here,
Monsieur Mgala.

27:43.520 --> 27:45.000
He is who you should thank.

27:45.040 --> 27:47.160
But as the local
do-gooding European,

27:47.200 --> 27:49.480
I get to be the one
to tell you.

27:49.520 --> 27:51.840
-[coughing in distance]
-How do you feel?

27:51.880 --> 27:55.160
[groaning]:
I... I feel great.

27:57.080 --> 28:00.400
No, it... it hurts.

28:00.440 --> 28:02.640
It hurts when I breathe.

28:02.680 --> 28:04.320
And... and it hurts

28:04.360 --> 28:07.760
when I don't breathe, too.
[groans]

28:07.800 --> 28:09.120
But, Doctor...

28:09.160 --> 28:12.080
my eyes.

28:12.120 --> 28:13.600
I can't...

28:13.640 --> 28:16.600
I can't see properly

28:16.640 --> 28:19.360
out the front, Doc.

28:19.400 --> 28:21.760
It's just... it's a blur.

28:21.800 --> 28:23.760
[grunts]

28:23.800 --> 28:27.000
Okay, just stay as still
as you can for me, hmm?

28:32.560 --> 28:35.000
I cannot be sure,
but I think perhaps it is

28:35.040 --> 28:36.640
the beginning
of a retinal hemorrhage.

28:36.680 --> 28:38.640
Both eyes, I would say.

28:38.680 --> 28:41.040
You will need
to be transferred to Kinshasa

28:41.080 --> 28:44.000
-when it is safe to move you.
-[grunts]

28:44.040 --> 28:46.760
Now, tell me,
is there someone we can call?

28:46.800 --> 28:48.560
-Hmm?
-Dominique.

28:48.600 --> 28:50.800
Is she here?

28:50.840 --> 28:54.200
Who? Is she a patient
at this hospital?

28:54.240 --> 28:56.760
No. From the flight.

28:56.800 --> 28:58.520
Sankuru.

28:58.560 --> 29:01.120
She was on the plane.
Dominique.

29:03.560 --> 29:05.360
[grunting]

29:12.760 --> 29:14.760
Do you mean her?

29:25.640 --> 29:27.800
She died?

29:27.840 --> 29:29.920
Yes.

29:29.960 --> 29:32.640
[panting] Why?

29:32.680 --> 29:35.480
She... she was not seen
at this hospital.

29:35.520 --> 29:39.280
I do not know more
than the news tells us.

29:42.120 --> 29:43.720
What happened to you?

29:43.760 --> 29:46.960
They say you were found
in the middle of the forest.

29:47.000 --> 29:50.240
[Ariel gasping softly]

29:53.880 --> 29:55.400
Mikael, can I ask you something?

29:55.440 --> 29:58.040
Were you in that plane?

29:58.080 --> 29:59.840
ARIEL:
I lied.

29:59.880 --> 30:04.520
And from that day on,
Mikael Aranson died.

30:04.560 --> 30:07.240
I became Ariel.

30:07.280 --> 30:10.160
The man in the paper
was the same one I saw

30:10.200 --> 30:11.840
in the airport.

30:11.880 --> 30:14.680
He handed a bag to that woman.

30:17.560 --> 30:19.520
In that bag was a laptop

30:19.560 --> 30:22.920
that blew a hole in the plane
and killed 85 people.

30:22.960 --> 30:24.520
Who was he?

30:24.560 --> 30:26.640
The paper didn't give a name.

30:26.680 --> 30:28.320
But I knew...

30:28.360 --> 30:32.680
I knew I couldn't tell anyone
what happened to me.

30:32.720 --> 30:36.360
Dominique had barely a scratch
on her when she left me.

30:36.400 --> 30:39.800
The paper said she died
of her injuries.

30:39.840 --> 30:42.000
And is that so impossible?

30:44.000 --> 30:46.160
You didn't see her.

30:46.200 --> 30:47.880
I did.

30:47.920 --> 30:51.840
Do you... do you think
she was killed?

30:51.880 --> 30:55.520
How better to make sure
no one could tell the truth?

30:55.560 --> 30:58.760
In the newspaper it said
a technical failure,

30:58.800 --> 31:00.840
nothing about a bomb.

31:00.880 --> 31:04.400
I may not be a smart man,
but I'm not a stupid one.

31:04.440 --> 31:08.240
I checked out of that hospital
as soon as I possibly could.

31:08.280 --> 31:11.680
And when I managed
to get across the border...

31:14.800 --> 31:18.280
...they said it was too late.

31:18.320 --> 31:21.960
The retinas in both my eyes
had completely hemorrhaged.

31:23.560 --> 31:25.800
I still think it was punishment.

31:25.840 --> 31:27.840
Losing my eyesight.

31:27.880 --> 31:30.160
For my silence.

31:31.720 --> 31:34.560
You're the only person
I've ever told this to.

31:34.600 --> 31:36.840
Everyone on that plane
was murdered,

31:36.880 --> 31:40.880
and you could have helped find
the people that did it.

31:40.920 --> 31:42.600
[whispers]:
I was scared.

31:42.640 --> 31:46.600
Not a day goes by that
I don't think about that.

31:46.640 --> 31:49.160
Listen, we don't know
each other very well,

31:49.200 --> 31:50.760
and this is j...

31:50.800 --> 31:52.480
I...

31:52.520 --> 31:53.920
I should go.

31:53.960 --> 31:57.160
My life is...
I'm just not this complicated.

31:57.200 --> 31:59.520
Maybe we should just
leave things as they were.

31:59.560 --> 32:01.160
Beatrix, please.

32:01.200 --> 32:02.640
I'm sorry.

32:02.680 --> 32:05.680
-Good-bye, Ariel.
-Oh, plea... please.

32:05.720 --> 32:07.160
Beatrix.

32:07.200 --> 32:09.200
♪ ♪

32:11.880 --> 32:13.920
[shuddering breath]

32:18.360 --> 32:20.600
[takes deep breath]

32:20.640 --> 32:23.040
♪ ♪

32:39.280 --> 32:41.280
FABRICE:
What is this?

32:44.000 --> 32:46.720
[both speaking Swahili]

32:50.520 --> 32:53.200
[both speaking Swahili]

33:00.840 --> 33:02.680
Okay. Okay.

33:02.720 --> 33:04.160
-What was that?
-He says up ahead

33:04.200 --> 33:06.960
is not a good idea;
there's militia there.

33:07.000 --> 33:09.520
-I thought you said
militia weren't a problem.
-Usually.

33:09.560 --> 33:11.280
But this is Liberation
of Rwanda forces.

33:11.320 --> 33:14.600
Hutus. Mostly, they are fine,
but... [chuckles]

33:14.640 --> 33:17.000
sometimes they can be
a little less predictable.

33:17.040 --> 33:19.680
TOM:
Yeah. They charge so-called, uh,

33:19.720 --> 33:23.360
fines, you know? They take
money and medical gear and...

33:23.400 --> 33:25.600
-Can we avoid them?
-FABRICE: Yes.

33:25.640 --> 33:26.760
He said we should take this road

33:26.800 --> 33:28.160
so we'll go around
the village okay.

33:28.200 --> 33:29.960
[ignition sputtering]

33:30.000 --> 33:31.040
No, no.

33:31.080 --> 33:32.600
[mutters in Swahili]

33:32.640 --> 33:35.360
-[groans]
-[ignition sputtering]

33:35.400 --> 33:39.480
So, don't you have
some questions for your article?

33:39.520 --> 33:41.680
Oh, you do speak English.

33:41.720 --> 33:44.640
When I choose.
So, some questions?

33:44.680 --> 33:46.440
It's not really like that.

33:46.480 --> 33:48.640
It's more a... observation.

33:48.680 --> 33:50.600
A few hours in the life of.

33:50.640 --> 33:52.520
You can just pretend
I'm not here.

33:52.560 --> 33:54.160
With pleasure.

33:54.200 --> 33:56.320
-[ignition sputtering]
-Come on. Come on.

33:56.360 --> 33:58.280
-[engine starts]
-["Magic" by Rocé playing]

33:58.320 --> 34:00.880
[chuckles]:
She's alive, huh?

34:00.920 --> 34:03.840
[man rapping in French]

34:29.120 --> 34:31.520
♪ ♪

34:33.400 --> 34:35.840
[music stops]

34:35.880 --> 34:37.240
Shit!

34:37.280 --> 34:38.640
So nothing can be done.

34:38.680 --> 34:41.400
This thing looks
like it's been here for years.

34:41.440 --> 34:43.080
You sure the old man told you
that we can get through

34:43.120 --> 34:44.800
-on this road?
-That's what he said.

34:44.840 --> 34:45.680
Don't move!

34:45.720 --> 34:46.880
Hey! Hey! Whoa! Hey.

34:46.920 --> 34:48.240
-[speaks Swahili]
-Okay, okay.

34:48.280 --> 34:49.840
Whoa. Okay, hey, hey, hey.

34:49.880 --> 34:52.320
We're doctors.
Look, look, look. Hey.

34:52.360 --> 34:55.760
Brothers, we're doctors. We are
taking medicine to Kisima.

34:57.240 --> 34:58.720
Shut up.
Empty your pockets.

34:58.760 --> 35:00.040
[groans, speaks Swahili]

35:00.080 --> 35:00.920
I said empty
your fucking pockets!

35:00.960 --> 35:02.400
I don't...

35:02.440 --> 35:03.200
Empty your pockets.

35:03.240 --> 35:04.680
Okay, okay.

35:04.720 --> 35:08.080
-I don't have anything.
-[shouting in Swahili]

35:13.840 --> 35:15.160
Okay, okay.

35:15.840 --> 35:17.600
[Fabrice groans]

35:17.640 --> 35:19.360
-TOM: Whoa, whoa.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
-Leave us the truck.

35:19.400 --> 35:20.200
It's okay.

35:20.240 --> 35:22.320
[ignition sputtering]

35:22.360 --> 35:25.040
It has our medicine...

35:25.080 --> 35:28.080
-Now we have nothing.
-[car door closes]

35:28.120 --> 35:30.520
Merde, merde!

35:30.560 --> 35:32.560
Fuck! What are we going to do?

35:32.600 --> 35:33.960
TOM:
Hey, just relax.

35:34.000 --> 35:36.200
Oh, Jesus.

35:36.240 --> 35:38.480
FABRICE: They've taken
our radios and everything.

35:40.440 --> 35:42.520
-[men shouting]
-[screaming]

35:42.560 --> 35:44.120
Let's go!

35:44.160 --> 35:45.760
[crying, shouting]

35:45.800 --> 35:48.440
Twende, twende, twende,
twende, twende, twende.

35:48.480 --> 35:49.960
[shouting]

36:08.520 --> 36:10.400
[screaming]

36:10.440 --> 36:13.080
[Djamba shouts in Swahili]

36:13.120 --> 36:15.520
[whimpering, crying]

36:20.960 --> 36:23.360
[birds chirping,
insects trilling]

36:34.400 --> 36:36.600
Is that your truck?

36:36.640 --> 36:38.520
FABRICE:
Yeah.

36:38.560 --> 36:41.200
[chuckling]

36:43.080 --> 36:44.800
[shouting in Swahili]

36:47.320 --> 36:49.560
-[Louise speaks French]
-Oh, shit.

36:49.600 --> 36:52.040
We don't want trouble.
We're going.

36:52.080 --> 36:53.600
[speaking Swahili]

36:56.240 --> 36:57.520
What? What are they saying?

36:57.560 --> 36:58.840
He's saying that the car
broke down last night

36:58.880 --> 37:00.120
and that he
can't start it again.

37:00.160 --> 37:02.360
-[stammers]
-[speaks Swahili]

37:02.400 --> 37:04.680
-We should fix it? You stole it!
-Hey.

37:04.720 --> 37:05.920
-[shouting]
-Please, please.

37:05.960 --> 37:07.520
Why should we fix it?

37:07.560 --> 37:10.720
-[groaning, grunting]
-What's happening?

37:10.760 --> 37:12.320
Okay.

37:12.360 --> 37:13.960
-Okay, okay.
-[shouts in Swahili]

37:14.000 --> 37:15.920
-Just do what he says. Okay?
-Okay.

37:15.960 --> 37:17.720
-[Fabrice coughing]
-Tom.
-Mon Dieu.

37:17.760 --> 37:20.240
TOM:
Everything's okay.

37:20.280 --> 37:22.240
Fabrice? Huh?

37:22.280 --> 37:24.520
-FABRICE: I'm okay.
-TOM: He's okay.

37:24.560 --> 37:27.360
PIETER:
Kalehe Mampata.

37:27.400 --> 37:29.560
I know you're here.

37:29.600 --> 37:30.840
Come forward!

37:30.880 --> 37:34.320
[chattering, whimpering]

37:43.120 --> 37:46.080
You've done a good job
for me, Kalehe.

37:46.120 --> 37:48.480
You should be proud of that.

37:48.520 --> 37:50.120
But things change.

37:50.160 --> 37:53.120
It's something we can't control.

37:53.160 --> 37:56.160
[speaking Swahili]

37:59.880 --> 38:01.920
He asks what you mean.
What has changed?

38:01.960 --> 38:04.560
Well, Kalehe,

38:04.600 --> 38:08.280
you can think of me
as being from the HR department.

38:11.240 --> 38:13.440
[speaks Swahili]

38:20.840 --> 38:23.480
No. I beg you, Mr. Bello.

38:23.520 --> 38:24.920
Please, Mr. Bello.

38:27.160 --> 38:29.560
No. No.

38:29.600 --> 38:32.560
[group whimpering, crying]

38:32.600 --> 38:34.960
You remember what I asked you?

38:37.200 --> 38:40.160
This is what we do to survive.

38:42.120 --> 38:44.480
[Tom and Fabrice
speaking indistinctly]

38:49.840 --> 38:52.720
TOM:
I'm helping, okay?

38:52.760 --> 38:54.360
We can't help.

39:01.400 --> 39:03.640
[speaking Swahili]

39:05.360 --> 39:07.320
I don't know what you're saying.

39:07.360 --> 39:09.600
[speaking Swahili]

39:13.720 --> 39:14.920
Stop it!

39:14.960 --> 39:16.120
Stop!
[shouts]

39:16.160 --> 39:18.120
[shouting]

39:18.160 --> 39:19.360
TOM:
Hey! [shouts in Swahili]

39:20.360 --> 39:21.640
Leave her alone. We're done.

39:21.680 --> 39:22.960
We're done.
Take the truck and go.

39:25.880 --> 39:29.600
[speaking Swahili]

39:29.640 --> 39:30.960
Want one of these girls
to keep us company?

39:31.000 --> 39:32.680
No! No! Don't take her.

39:32.720 --> 39:33.920
-[overlapping shouting]
-No.

39:38.200 --> 39:39.720
[shouting continues]

39:39.760 --> 39:42.400
-[shouting]
-Please!

39:42.440 --> 39:46.320
Mr. Bello, I beg you.

39:46.360 --> 39:50.360
Please let me live!

39:50.400 --> 39:52.080
Please
let me live!

39:52.120 --> 39:55.480
♪ ♪

40:00.320 --> 40:02.840
[shouting]

40:02.880 --> 40:04.960
-[grunts]
-[groans]

40:05.000 --> 40:06.600
-[grunts]
-Oh, no, no, no.

40:06.640 --> 40:08.680
[grunting]

40:08.720 --> 40:09.760
Georgia.

40:11.680 --> 40:13.440
Georgia.

40:13.480 --> 40:16.080
[panting]

40:18.480 --> 40:21.560
[panting]

40:25.440 --> 40:27.840
[shouting]

40:30.000 --> 40:31.800
[whimpering]

40:31.840 --> 40:33.960
-[gunshot]
-[screaming]

40:34.000 --> 40:36.040
♪ ♪

40:37.800 --> 40:39.720
[panting]

40:39.760 --> 40:42.080
-[gun drops]
-[Louise speaks indistinctly]

40:42.120 --> 40:44.960
[Georgia gasping]

40:49.800 --> 40:51.320
[women crying]

40:51.360 --> 40:53.520
You can open your eyes now.

40:53.560 --> 40:55.920
[woman shouting, wailing]

40:55.960 --> 40:58.560
[whimpers]

40:58.600 --> 41:01.160
PIETER:
Things are different now.

41:01.200 --> 41:03.120
[Djamba translates in Swahili]

41:03.160 --> 41:05.360
[shouts in Swahili]

41:05.400 --> 41:07.800
-[woman crying]
-[men shouting]

41:21.320 --> 41:24.680
[woman crying]

41:24.720 --> 41:27.760
[shouting, sobbing]

41:53.880 --> 41:57.440
[speaks Icelandic]

41:57.480 --> 41:59.040
[line beeps]

41:59.080 --> 42:02.440
[recorded message of Beatrix
speaking foreign language]

42:02.480 --> 42:03.440
[line beeps]

42:03.480 --> 42:04.680
Hey, Beatrix.

42:04.720 --> 42:07.840
Hey, it's, uh, Ariel.

42:07.880 --> 42:09.560
I'm leaving today.

42:09.600 --> 42:10.880
I moved my flight up.

42:10.920 --> 42:14.280
So, uh... this is it.

42:14.320 --> 42:17.080
I know I disappointed you.

42:17.120 --> 42:18.640
Whatever you feel,

42:18.680 --> 42:21.600
just know that I disappointed
myself even more.

42:21.640 --> 42:23.360
I made a mistake.

42:23.400 --> 42:25.160
It was...

42:25.200 --> 42:28.760
it was stupid and selfish,
but there it is.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.400
I must live with it.

42:34.000 --> 42:36.400
It was nice to know you.

42:37.760 --> 42:39.520
I promise
I won't bother you again.

42:39.560 --> 42:42.400
But I hope your operation, uh...

42:42.440 --> 42:45.760
I hope you open your eyes
and you see the world

42:45.800 --> 42:49.200
and all the beautiful things
that live upon it.

42:51.240 --> 42:55.600
I hope you get to see
Whistler's Mother.

42:55.640 --> 42:57.840
[knocking at door]

42:59.720 --> 43:01.880
Good-bye.

43:01.920 --> 43:02.920
Come in.

43:05.320 --> 43:07.760
Mr. Helgason, you wanted someone
to pack your bag?

43:07.800 --> 43:09.960
Please, if it's not
too much trouble.

43:10.000 --> 43:11.440
Of course.

43:11.480 --> 43:13.200
But before that,
there's someone here to see you.

43:27.000 --> 43:29.440
Thank you.

43:29.480 --> 43:31.760
Mr. Helgason.

43:31.800 --> 43:34.200
My name is Martin Benson.

43:34.240 --> 43:36.200
Um, I'm sorry, have we met?

43:36.240 --> 43:37.400
Um, I don't remember.

43:37.440 --> 43:39.240
No, no, we've never met before.

43:39.280 --> 43:41.840
And I'm sorry to disturb you
like this.

43:41.880 --> 43:44.200
But I needed to talk to you

43:44.240 --> 43:48.280
about Sankuru Airways Flight 19.

43:48.320 --> 43:52.400
I know who you are,
and I know what you've done.
